Eminent elder statesmen and some state actors, who include former President Olusegun Obasanjo, Vice President Yemi Osinbajo, former President of the Senate, Dr. Bukola Saraki, renowned businessman and philanthropist, Aliko Dangote; Governor Godwin Obaseki of Edo State, Governor Babajide Sanwo-Olu of Lagos State, and others assembled at Odoragunshin, Epe, Lagos, on Sunday, celebrate Lady Christine Doja Otedola, mother of Femi Otedola, on her 90th birthday.
The former First Lady of Lagos State, Doja, was eulogized for her values, which include Christianity, charity, and community, including her glowing personality conceived as a resonating trait of simplicity.
Other dignitaries at the birthday anniversary included the Governor Dapo Abiodun of Ogun State,  the Governor of the Central Bank of Nigeria, Godwin Emefiele; Chairman of Heirs Holdings, Tony Elumelu; former Governor of Anambra State, Peter Obi; etc.
